## 🔧 Technical Concepts Explained

### Content-Based vs Collaborative Filtering

| Aspect | Content-Based Filtering | Collaborative Filtering |
|--------|------------------------|------------------------|
| **Driven by** | Item attributes | Community behavior |
| **How it works** | Maps user preferences to item properties | Identifies patterns among similar users |
| **Data needed** | Item metadata only | Historical user interactions |
| **Cold Start** | Handles new items easily | Struggles with new users/items |

**Project 3 uses Content-Based Filtering**

---

### TF-IDF Vectorization

Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) transforms text into numerical vectors:

| Term | TF (Term Frequency) | IDF (Inverse Document Frequency) |
|------|--------------------|----------------------------------|
| Python | High in Data Science roles | Medium (appears frequently) |
| obscure_skill | Low in individual docs | High (rare, thus important) |

**Formula:** `TF-IDF = Term Frequency × log(Total Documents / Documents with term)`

---

### Cosine Similarity

Measures the **angle** between two vectors, ignoring magnitude:

| Similarity Score | Interpretation |
|------------------|----------------|
| 1.0 | Perfect match (same direction) |
| 0.7-0.9 | Strong match |
| 0.4-0.6 | Moderate match |
| 0.0 | No match (perpendicular) |
| -1.0 | Opposite direction (not possible with TF-IDF) |

